## Description

Fixes #296.

The resolver Deployment informer's `DeleteFunc` was a TODO ā€” it logged a warning but took no reconciliation action. As a result, deleting the resolver Deployment (via `helm uninstall`, `kubectl delete deployment`, namespace deletion, etc.) while any `ElastiService` was in proxy mode left the hijacked EndpointSlices pointing at now-dead resolver pod IPs. All traffic to affected services silently timed out with no error surfaced anywhere the operator could see.

This PR implements the first option from the TODO comment ("move to the serve mode") for the case where the resolver Deployment has been cleanly deleted. When the informer fires `DeleteFunc`, the operator now enumerates all services currently in proxy mode via `crddirectory.CRDDirectory.Services` and switches each to serve mode using the existing `switchMode(ctx, req, values.ServeMode)` code path ā€” the same one used for normal proxy ā†’ serve transitions.

## Type of change

- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking change which fixes an issue)

## How the fix works

Two-pass iteration inside a new `handleResolverDeletion` method:

1. **First pass** counts services currently in proxy mode. If the count is zero, log the warning and return early. If non-zero, the count is included in the log line so operators can see at a glance how many services were affected.

2. **Second pass** switches each proxy-mode service to serve mode. Iteration is best-effort ā€” if `switchMode` fails for one service, the error is logged with the service identifier and iteration continues, so a single broken service can't prevent recovery of others.

Both passes use the defensive assertion pattern (`, ok :=` on type assertions, nil checks on pointers, length check on the split key) so any unexpected value in the `CRDDirectory` results in a logged error and a skipped entry rather than a panic that would crash the operator process.

`switchMode` internally handles the case of a service that's already in serve mode (via `deleteEndpointsliceToResolver`'s `IsNotFound` check and `updateCRDStatus`'s merge-patch semantics), so there's no race concern if a service transitions between the filter check and the mode switch.

